When a user's browser has cookies disabled, and they try to login to JIRA, the login page just refreshes. There is no message to the user indicating what is wrong.  It would be helpful, if you can say something like "You browser has cookies disabled, you need to enable cookies to login to JIRA."

Some users would like alphanumeric String in summary to be further tokenized, e.g. Invoice-777-ABC ZYX-999 is tokenized to:

{noformat}
Invoice-777-ABC
ZYX-999
{noformat}

Hence searching for 777 or 999 will not return any matched results.

Currently JIRA's EnglishAnalyzer is using the StandardTokenizer. And the example above occurs due to the matches on:
* {{<ALPHANUM> <P> <HAS_DIGIT>}}
* {{<ALPHANUM> (<P> <HAS_DIGIT> <P> <ALPHANUM>)+}}

